The ACM SIGPLAN 6th Workshop on Programming Languages and Analysis for Security(PLAS) was held on June 5, 2011 as a satellite event of PLDI 2011 in San Jose, California, USA. The call for papers attracted 18 submissions, of which five full papers and three position papers were selected for presentation at the workshop and inclusion in these proceedings. The workshop also featured invited talks by Ulfar Erlingsson of Google and Dawn Song of University of California, Berkeley.